amdgpu: gmc_v7_0 — B1.1-α drop the DEPTH=0 override now that UVD is soft-fail

β-2-A (0040) forced VC1_CNTL.PAGE_TABLE_DEPTH = 0 on Liverpool/Gladius to
collapse VC1..VC15 to a flat-GART walk. The whole purpose of that hack
was to let the UVD VCPU firmware read GPU VA 0x300000000 via a single
PTE we bound in the shared GART. It served its purpose during the
A-arc — we proved the fw could reach that VA.

After 17 UVD iterations + the Orbis dungeon mapping established that
UVD bring-up is structurally blocked on SBL/SAMU access (see
checkpoint/docs/research/orbis-dungeon/rooms/sbl-driver.md), A18 and
A19 soft-failed UVD and VCE hw_init so amdgpu probe completes. Nothing
on the live kernel actually does the 0x300000000 access anymore.

What DEPTH=0 was *still* costing us: amdgpu_vm's per-vmid PT_BASE_ADDR
writes (emitted by cik_emit_vm_flush before every ring submission)
were silently ignored. The GMC kept walking the flat GART for VC1..VC15
even though the per-vm subsystem had a real PD for each VMID. When
Hyprland's CPF tried to read its userspace IB at GPU VA 0x268000 in
VMID 1, the lookup hit a flat-GART hole (page 616 is in the void
between amdgpu_gart_bind regions) and faulted:

  VM_CONTEXT1_PROTECTION_FAULT_ADDR    0x00000268
  VM_CONTEXT1_PROTECTION_FAULT_STATUS  0x0207600C
  VM fault (0x0c, vmid 1, pasid 0) at page 616, read from 'CPF'

Then "ring gfx timeout" → "Ring gfx reset failure" → GPU reset cascade
→ gfx_v7_0_suspend → desktop dies. This is what's been blocking
Hyprland / any GL-rendered Wayland session even though software-Pixman
Weston works fine.

The fix: stop forcing DEPTH=0. Leave the mainline DEPTH=1 write (line
742, untouched) in place and let amdgpu_vm do its per-vmid PD job
normally. The two flat-GART dummy binds (VA 0x300000000, VA 0) and
the UVD fw mirror bind from 0042 all become dead under DEPTH=1 since
VC1..VC15 stop consulting the flat GART — keeping them defensively
costs one PTE each and shields VC0-routed kernel reads if any.

Expected hardware signals:

  ✅ amdgpu probe still completes; UVD/VCE still soft-fail per A18/A19.
  ✅ "VM fault ... vmid 1 ... page 616 ... CPF" disappears.
  ✅ "ring gfx timeout / reset failure" disappears.
  ✅ Hyprland (or any GL Wayland compositor) survives past first frame.
  🟡 A different VM fault on some other VMID/page — mainline per-vm
     is working but something else needs a bind. We narrow.
  ❌ Same page-616 CPF fault — DEPTH=1 isn't the gate; per-vm flush
     isn't reaching VC1_PT_BASE on this hardware. Fall back to B1.1-β
     (build a real per-vmid PD with low-VA flat-GART mirror).
  💀 amdgpu probe regresses — we accidentally relied on DEPTH=0 for
     some other path. Revert this patch and investigate.

Cost: −6 lines of code (one RREG32/WREG32 + DRM_INFO), 20 lines of
comment.

Signed-off-by: Meerzulee <mirzaali@screeninternational.org>

--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/gmc_v7_0.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/gmc_v7_0.c
@@ -779,12 +779,26 @@
 	if (adev->asic_type == CHIP_LIVERPOOL || adev->asic_type == CHIP_GLADIUS) {
 		dma_addr_t fw_dummy = adev->dummy_page_addr;

-		tmp = RREG32(mmVM_CONTEXT1_CNTL);
-		tmp = REG_SET_FIELD(tmp, VM_CONTEXT1_CNTL,
-				    PAGE_TABLE_DEPTH, 0);
-		WREG32(mmVM_CONTEXT1_CNTL, tmp);
-		DRM_INFO("ps4: VC1..VC15 PAGE_TABLE_DEPTH overridden to 0 "
-			 "(flat walk) for UVD compatibility\n");
+		/*
+		 * v76e-B1.1-α: restore mainline VC1..VC15 PAGE_TABLE_DEPTH=1.
+		 *
+		 * β-2-A's DEPTH=0 forced a flat-GART walk so the UVD fw could
+		 * read GPU VA 0x300000000 via a single PTE we bound in the
+		 * shared GART. That trick is no longer needed: A18 + A19 now
+		 * soft-fail UVD and VCE bring-up, so nothing ever does the
+		 * 0x300000000 access. With DEPTH=0 still asserted, amdgpu_vm's
+		 * per-vmid PT_BASE writes were silently ignored — GFX VMID 1's
+		 * CPF read of a userspace IB fell into a flat-GART hole and
+		 * faulted at page 616 (VA 0x268000), killing Hyprland.
+		 *
+		 * Leaving DEPTH=1 alone lets amdgpu_vm program per-vmid PDs the
+		 * way mainline expects on every submission. The dummy bind
+		 * below at flat-GART VA 0x300000000 (plus the VA-0 bind that
+		 * follows for null-deref safety) becomes inert under DEPTH=1
+		 * since VC1..VC15 stop consulting the flat GART — kept here
+		 * defensively in case any VC0-routed kernel path still reaches
+		 * those addresses.
+		 */

 		amdgpu_gart_bind(adev, 0x300000000ULL, 1, &fw_dummy,
 				 AMDGPU_PTE_VALID | AMDGPU_PTE_SYSTEM |
